			as to the procedure for applying for leave, or making a reference, undersection 71B(5A) or (5B) of this Act;
			as to circumstances in which the jurisdiction of the court may be exercisedby a judge advocate appointed under section 52FG of this Act sitting alone;
			enabling an uncontested appeal to be determined without a hearing;
			as to the convening and constitution of the court to hear any appeal;
			as to circumstances in which officers otherwise qualified under section52FH of this Act are ineligible to hear particular appeals;
			enabling the appellant to object to members of the court;
			as to the representation of the appellant on the hearing of appeals undersection 52FK of this Act and at any preliminary proceedings;
			as to the admissibility of evidence;
			as to the rehearing of an appeal where any member of the court originallyconstituted to hear it has been unable to continue hearing the appeal;
			as to procuring the attendance of witnesses at the hearing of appeals andat any preliminary proceedings;
			as to the administration of oaths;
			as to the recording of the proceedings of the court and custody of recordsof the proceedings;
			as to making copies of the records of proceedings available and as to thefees payable for such copies;
			as to the procedure for applying to have a case stated under section52FN(2) of this Act.
		Rules under this section may provide for any enactment which relates to thepractice or procedure of courts-martial or to the admissibility of evidence incourts-martial to apply in relation to the court with such modifications asmay be specified.
		Rules under this section shall be made by statutory instrument subject toannulment in pursuance of a resolution of either House of Parliament.”
